<HL>
   Economic Summit (A Special Report): Postscript
   ---
   Loose Lips
   ----
   By Philip Revzin
</HL>
<DATE>
07/09/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE R26
</SO>
<LP>
   SO MUCH TO talk about. And so little nerve. The
contentious issues seem endless. A unified Germany. A unified
Europe. The end of the U.S.-British special relationship.
U.S.-Japanese trade squabbles. EC trade squabbles with just
about everybody. At the end of their meeting, the summit
leaders will issue a communique saying everything is just
splendid. But before they do, imagine some of the private
conversations -- even if they're probably too candid ever to
occur.
   (See accompanying comic strip -- WSJ July 9, 1990)
</LP>
