<LP>
   OTTAWA -- Canadian steel ingot production totaled 280,137
metric tons in the week ended June 30, down 2.6% from 287,537
tons in the preceding week and down 0.5% from 281,421 tons a
year earlier, Statistics Canada, a federal agency, said.
   A metric ton equals about 2,204.6 pounds. For the year
through June 30, production totaled 7,266,572 metric tons,
down 8.8% from 7,971,417 tons a year earlier.
