<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   TOKYO -- Sumitomo Cement Co. established a joint venture
in South Korea to produce calcium carbonate, a material used
to make better-quality printing paper, company officials
said.
   The joint company, Korea Fimatic Co., is capitalized at
one billion won ($1.4 million) and is 60%-owned by a local
concern, Korea Electric Chemical Co., and 20% each by
Sumitomo Cement and Fimatic Ltd., a Japanese chemical
company.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The joint venture this month will start building a plant
capable of producing 3,000 tons of calcium carbonate a month
and will sell the product to paper companies in South Korea.
The plant is to go into operation next February.
