<HL>
   Economic Summit (A Special Report): By the Numbers
   ---
   Snapshot of the Seven:
   A Statistical Portrait of the Summit Countries
</HL>
<DATE>
07/09/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE R16
</SO>
<CO>
   CANDA JAPAN EUROP
</CO>
<IN>
INTERNATIONAL ECONOMIC NEWS AND STATISTICS (IEN)
</IN>
<LP>
   BY ANY MEASURE, the seven summit countries carry enormous
economic clout. Together, they account for about 55% of world
gross national product, 54% of world exports and 55% of world
imports. Income per capita in the seven countries ranges from
$12,810 to $21,020. Here's a closer look at how the seven
stack up.
   ---
                       Per-Capita GNP
                                                                                                       

</LP>
<TEXT>
   GNP per person, based on 1989-90 data, in U.S. dollars.
Comparing the Summit Seven with an array of poorer nations.
                                                                                                       

