<HL>
   Business Brief -- Sun Sportswear Inc.:
   Second-Quarter Sales Fell
   Up to 12%; Weather Cited
</HL>
<DATE>
07/09/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A4B
</SO>
<CO>
   SSPW
</CO>
<LP>
   Sun Sportswear Inc., Kent, Wash., one of the nation's
largest screen-printers of casual sportswear sold in discount
retail stores, said cool spring weather caused second-quarter
sales to drop between 9% and 12% to an estimated $22 million
to $23 million from $25.1 million a year earlier.
   Officials attributed the poor performance to slowing
orders and an inventory buildup. Earnings and sales data
won't be available until the end of the month, a spokeswoman
said. But, reflecting the sales slump, Sun Sportswear shares
plunged $1.25, to close at $8.25, in national
over-the-counter trading Friday.
</LP>
