<HL>
   Business Brief -- CMS Energy Corp.:
   Curbs Lifted on Firm's Use
   Of Debt, Equity in Plant
</HL>
<DATE>
07/09/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C11
</SO>
<CO>
   CMS
</CO>
<GV>
JUSTICE DEPARTMENT (JUS)
</GV>
<LP>
   CMS Energy Corp. said a Michigan circuit court judge
removed restrictions on the company's use of its $1.5 billion
of debt and equity interests in the Midland Cogeneration
Venture.
   But the court said that CMS's Consumer's Power Co. utility
unit must maintain a $450 million corporate bond, as ordered
earlier by Michigan regulators.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   In its ruling, the court removed all restrictions on the
use by Dearborn, Mich.-based CMS of the $1.2 billion in notes
and $300 million in equity it received in return for its
contribution to the cogeneration venture. The venture is a
1,380-megawatt power plant converted from CMS's failed effort
to build a nuclear plant in Midland.
   The court action also relieved CMS of having to file a
$100 million surety bond previously required by another
court.
   CMS said the decision will become effective Aug. 3, and
the company isn't planning an appeal.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>
WSJ900709-0045
</DOCNO>
<DOCID>
900709-0045.
</DOCID>
<HL>
   Business Brief -- Peoples Bancorp of Worcester:
   Deposits of a Savings Bank
   To Be Bought From FDIC
</HL>
<DATE>
07/09/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B7D
</SO>
<CO>
   PEBW
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
BANKS (BNK)
</IN>
<GV>
FEDERAL GOVERNMENT (FDL)
</GV>
<LP>
   Peoples Bancorp of Worcester Inc., a bank holding company,
said it agreed to acquire about $300 million in insured
deposits of Milford, Mass.-based Milford Savings Bank from
the Federal Deposit Insurance Corp.
   Milford Savings was declared insolvent and closed by the
Massachusetts banking commissioner on Friday.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Under the agreement, Peoples Bancorp, based in Worcester,
Mass., will assume Milford Savings' total deposit liability
of about $300 million from the FDIC for a premium of
$100,000. Peoples Bancorp also will have the option, for 90
days, to buy certain loans after reviewing Milford's loan
portfolio. Peoples Bancorp said the five Milford Savings
offices will reopen as Peoples Bancorp branches today.
   The Milford acquisition is Peoples Bancorp's second
regulatory-assisted acquisition of a failed Massachusetts
bank. In April 1989, the company assumed certain assets and
the deposits of Leominster, Mass.-based First Service Bank
for Savings, which was closed by the state banking
commissioner in March 1989.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
