<LP>
   Xicor Inc., Milpitas, Calif., reported a loss of $4.8
million, or 26 cents a share, for the second quarter ending
June 17. The company had net income of $2.2 million, or 12
cents a share, in the year-earlier quarter.
   Citing failure to meet some of its orders, the company
said net sales were down to $20.4 million from $22 million a
year ago.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   For the first half of fiscal 1990, the manufacturer of
semiconductors and related devices reported a loss of $11.8
million, or 65 cents a share. In the year-earlier first half,
the company had net income of $5.2 million, or 28 cents a
share.
   Company President Raphael Klein said the concern was
unable to meet orders because of manufacturing difficulties
that have plagued it for several quarters. The company has
recently completed a $50 million factory renovation.
