   Switzerland's Inflation Rate
</HL>
<DATE>
07/09/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B3
</SO>
<CO>
   EUROP
</CO>
<LP>
   BERN -- Switzerland's cost-of-living index in June inched
up 0.1% from May and rose 5% from a year earlier, the
government said, noting that more favorable oil and energy
prices helped slow the pace of inflation.
   The increases represented a slowdown from May's rises of
0.5% from the preceding month and 5.1% from a year earlier.
